SARS-CoV is similar to its homologous virus, which caused SARS in several thousand people in 2003, SARS-CoV-2 can also be transmitted from bats and cause the same symptoms through the same mechanism.
However, COVID-19 has a lower severity and mortality than SARS but is much more contagious and affects older people than younger and men more than women.
