The virus is highly homologous to the coronavirus (CoV) that caused the outbreak of severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS) in 2003; thus, on February 11, 2020, it was renamed SARS-CoV-2 by the World Health Organization (WHO), and the associated disease was named CoV disease-19 (COVID-19).
The outbreak started in Wuhan, China and quickly spread across the country and to 50 other countries around the world.
