CoVs are traditionally considered non-lethal pathogens in humans, causing about 15% of the common cold cases.
However, in this century, we have twice been exposed to highly pathogenic bacterial human CoVs, namely SARS-CoV and MERS-CoV, which started an epidemic outbreak in China in 2003 and in Saudi Arabia in 2012 respectively, and which soon spread to many other countries with dire symptoms and mortality.
Thus, the current COVID-19 is the third recorded CoV outbreak in human history.
