Diarrhoea and pneumonia are the cause of the deaths of about 3.5 million children a year.
According to UNICEF, a change to the firm practice of washing hands with soap before eating and after using the toilet could save more lives than any single vaccine or medical intervention, cut deaths from diarrhea by almost half and deaths from acute respiratory infections by a quarter.
Hand washing is integrated with other sanitation systems as part of the Water, Sanitation and Hygiene (WASH) programmes.
