Workplace risk controls for COVID-19 are the application of occupational safety and health practices to manage risks to prevent the spread of coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19).
Appropriate workplace risk controls depend on the workplace and the work to be done, a risk assessment of sources of exposure, the severity of disease in the community, and the risk factors of individual workers who may be at risk of COVID-19.
